modules.description: Provides functions for line editing, history management, and input completion, using a self-contained implementation of linenoise. Works with strings, lists, and custom input handlers to process user input interactively. Enables command-line interfaces with features like arrow key navigation and history recall without external dependencies.

Provides functions for line editing, tab completion, and history management in a terminal. Works with strings, completions, and hint_color to enable interactive command-line features. Supports adding, saving, and loading history, setting hints, and handling keyboard signals.
